Police had the gruesome task of retrieving a decomposed body which was discovered floating in the Umbilo River near Eden Road, in Pinetown, earlier today (Tuesday, 27 October). Police officers from Durban Search and Rescue along with Durban K9 Search and Rescue and Metro Police Search and Rescue were called out to Paradise Valley in Pinetown. Police spokesperson, Captain Nqobile Gwala, said: “The decomposed body of an unknown male was seen floating in the Umbilo River near Eden Road by a passerby. The body was recovered and carried out to the roadway where it was handed over to police officers from Pinetown. An inquest was opened for investigation.” 